        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 4:01PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 401 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles east of Monida, or 18 miles north of Idmon, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lakeview.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
